                '## PPE & Glove Protocol\n\n### Required PPE for Every Procedure\n1. **Nitrile gloves** — Latex-free, powder-free, medical grade\n2. **Face mask** — Minimum Level 1 barrier\n3. **Protective eyewear** — When splash risk exists\n4. **Disposable apron or lab coat** — Changed between clients\n\n### Glove Change Protocol\nGloves must be changed:\n- Between clients (always)\n- When torn or punctured\n- After touching non-sterile surfaces (phone, light switch, chair adjustment)\n- Before re-entering the sterile field after any interruption\n\n### Double-Gloving\nDouble-gloving provides an additional barrier and is recommended during training. Change the outer glove when contaminated while maintaining the inner barrier.',
