                '## Contraindications\n\n### Absolute Contraindications (Do NOT proceed)\n- **Pregnancy or nursing** — liability and healing concerns\n- **Active skin conditions** at the treatment site (eczema, psoriasis, rosacea flare)\n- **Blood-thinning medications** (Warfarin, Heparin) without physician clearance\n- **Accutane use** within the last 12 months\n- **Active infections** or fever\n- **Autoimmune disorders** without physician clearance\n- **Keloid-prone scarring** at the treatment site\n\n### Relative Contraindications (Proceed with caution)\n- Diabetes (Type 1 or 2) — may affect healing\n- High blood pressure — controlled with medication is usually acceptable\n- Recent Botox or filler — wait 2-4 weeks\n- Recent chemical peel or laser — wait until fully healed\n- Iron deficiency anemia — may affect pigment retention\n\n### When in Doubt\nAlways err on the side of caution. Request a physician clearance letter when the situation is ambiguous. It is better to postpone than to cause harm.',
