                '## The Four Healing Stages\n\n### Stage 1: Inflammatory (Days 1-3)\n- Redness, swelling, tenderness\n- Color appears very dark and bold\n- Lymph fluid may weep slightly\n- Client should blot gently, no touching\n\n### Stage 2: Scabbing (Days 3-7)\n- Thin film or flaky scab forms\n- Color may appear patchy underneath\n- **Critical: Do NOT pick or peel scabs**\n- Keep area dry per aftercare protocol\n\n### Stage 3: Ghosting (Days 7-14)\n- Scabs fall off naturally\n- Pigment appears faded or \"disappeared\"\n- This is NORMAL — pigment is healing under new skin\n- Client anxiety is highest here — prepare them\n\n### Stage 4: True Color (Days 28-42)\n- Skin fully regenerates over the pigment\n- True healed color emerges\n- This is when touch-up assessment should occur\n- Color is typically 30-50% lighter than fresh application',
